.TH "cpuidle_coupled_set_waiting" 9 "cpuidle_coupled_set_waiting" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cpuidle_coupled_set_waiting \- mark this cpu as in the wait loop
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" cpuidle_coupled_set_waiting
.BI "(int cpu "  ","
.BI "struct cpuidle_coupled *coupled "  ","
.BI "int next_state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cpu" 12
target cpu
.IP "coupled" 12
the struct coupled that contains the current cpu
.IP "next_state" 12
the index in drv->states of the requested state for this cpu
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Updates the requested idle state for the specified cpuidle device.
Returns the number of waiting cpus.
